  "text": "There has been some recent work on the stochastic version of the IAG method (called stochastic average gradient, or SAG) where we sample the component function to update instead of using a cyclic order [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] . Unlike the IAG method where the linear convergence rate depends on the number of passes through the data, the SAG method achieves a linear convergence rate that depends on the number of iterations. Further, when the number of training examples is sufficiently large, the SAG method allows the use of a very large step-size, which leads to improved theoretical and empirical performance.",
